<p>I am using dynamic mapping in ElasticSearch.  </p>  <p>I use it because my index is long and I need to use the template feature in order to avoid updating definitions in multiple places (<a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/32518081/elasticsearch-static-mapping-vs-dynamic-mapping-when-using-templates">see my other SO question</a>).  </p>  <p>I am sending the following json (Object Zoo) which <strong>contains a HashMap</strong> as an example:  </p>  <pre><code>Put 127.0.0.1:9200/myIndex/Zoo/10 {   "id" : 1,   "Name" : "Madagascar",   "map" : {     "1" : {       "id" : -4944060986111146989,       "name" : null     },     "2" : {       "id" : 5073063561743125202,       "name" : null     },     "3" : {       "id" : -1777985506870671559,       "name" : null     }   } } </code></pre>  <p>This creates the following Index  </p>  <pre><code>{     "mm3_v2": {         "mappings": {             "Zoo": {                 "properties": {                     "Name": {                         "type": "string"                     },                     "id": {                         "type": "long"                     },                     "map": {                         "properties": {                             "1": {                                 "properties": {                                     "id": {                                         "type": "long"                                     }                                 }                             },                             "2": {                                 "properties": {                                     "id": {                                         "type": "long"                                     }                                 }                             },                             "3": {                                 "properties": {                                     "id": {                                         "type": "long"                                     }                                 }                             }                         }                     }                 }             }         }     } } </code></pre>  <p>In this example the inner object in the hashmap is short.<br> In real life my hashmap's object can be long.  </p>  <p>This can create a huge index files (easily 1M rows) and for each object it repeats exactly the same definition.<br> (e.g. when stored in a list, the mapping does not repeat itself)  </p>  <p>Is there a way to properly define a hashmap in elastic search?  </p>